 early Victorian age. This book will become essential reading for historians and students interested in the industrial revolution, transport, and the unique history of Manchester, the world’s first industrial city.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCanalszEnglandzManchester. 0aIndustrial revolutionzEnglandzManchester. 0aIndustrializationzEnglandzManchester. 0aUrban transportationzEnglandzManchester. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aBritish Industrial Revolution.  aBritish cotton industry.  aManchester.  acanal transport.  aconsumerism.  aeconomic impact.  aindustrialisation.  arail transport.  aregional history.  aroad transport.  atrade.  aurban development.1 aMaw, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130471423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130471/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles